    <Heading>
    Writing Secure Code
    </Heading>
    <List>
    <ListItem>Good security cannot be tacked on to a product after the fact,
    it must be designed in.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    A bug anywhere in the product can create a security vulnerability.
    We need secure code, not security code.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    Writing secure code is an integral and necessary part of writing correct code.
    It is as important as good performance and good memory management.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    In short, security is everyone's responsibility.
    </ListItem>
    </List>
